In fusions systems that are in thermal equilibrium the particles are in a Maxwell‚ÄìBoltzmann distribution, meaning the particles have a range of energies centered around the plasma temperature. The sun, magnetically confined plasmas and inertial confinement fusion systems are well modeled to be in a thermal equilibrium. In these cases, the value of interest is the fusion cross section averaged across the Maxwell-Boltzmann distribution. The Naval Research Lab's plasma physics formulary tabulates Maxwell averaged fusion cross sections reactivities in formula_21.

